# Third-Party Notices

hippo's own source is MIT-licensed (see [LICENSE](LICENSE)). hippo does **not**
bundle or redistribute third-party source code — the pre-bootstrap fallbacks in
`plugin/memory/_vendor/` (a BM25 scorer and a frontmatter parser) are original MIT
implementations, not copied vendor code.

This file inventories the third-party components hippo **depends on at runtime**:
the Python packages the `/hippo:bootstrap` step installs from PyPI into a
standalone plugin venv, and the sentence-embedding model it downloads on first
index build. None of these is committed to this repository or shipped inside the
plugin bundle; each is fetched from its own distribution, and that distribution's
license text travels with the artifact. `pip show <name>` (or the wheel's own
LICENSE) on a bootstrapped venv is the authoritative source for any entry here.

Every runtime dependency is permissively licensed — Apache-2.0, MIT, BSD-3-Clause,
MPL-2.0, or HPND (MIT-CMU). There is no copyleft obligation on hippo's own code.

