## Embedding model

Dense recall uses a sentence-embedding model downloaded (~130 MB) on the first
`build_index` run and cached offline thereafter — never committed to git, never
shipped in the plugin bundle. `fastembed` fetches a quantized-ONNX repackaging of
the model from the Hugging Face Hub.

| Role | Model (card) | License | Artifact fetched by fastembed |
|------|--------------|---------|-------------------------------|
| Default (English) | [`BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5`](https://huggingface.co/BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5) | MIT | [`qdrant/bge-small-en-v1.5-onnx-q`](https://huggingface.co/qdrant/bge-small-en-v1.5-onnx-q) |
| `--multilingual` preset | [`sentence-transformers/paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2`](https://huggingface.co/sentence-transformers/paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2) | Apache-2.0 | [`qdrant/paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2-onnx-Q`](https://huggingface.co/qdrant/paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM-L12-v2-onnx-Q) |

Each ONNX repackaging carries the same license as its source model. See
`plugin/memory/build_index.py` (`_HF_SOURCE_REPO_BY_MODEL`, `resolve_embed_model`)
for the exact model resolution and cache paths, and `HIPPO_EMBED_MODEL` to override
the model.
